Thanks. I am not opposed to making these changes, but in order to effectively resolve this issue I really need to understand the use case you have that makes this change necessary.

With styling a component inside of Vue, you should be able to use scoped styles so that you do not need to add these long global selectors:

```css
ion-app > ion-modal > .modal-wrapper > .ion-page > ion-header,
ion-app > ion-modal > .modal-wrapper > .ion-page > .ion-page > ion-header {
