}
```

Alternatively, if you want to style _all_ modals globally you still should not need to write out these long selectors. You should be able to just target `ion-modal ion-header` directly. You might run into issues with CSS specificity, but we plan on addressing this for `ion-modal` and `ion-popover` in Framework v6. One thought instead is to set a class on the modals and target that class instead of a generic `ion-modal` selector.

Could you try those alternatives and let me know if it helps at all?

