@ptmkenny 

The problem is that the **IonTabs** component checks if at least one it's direct children is type of **IonTabBar** (see https://github.com/ionic-team/ionic-framework/blob/v5.9.1/packages/react/src/components/navigation/IonTabs.tsx#L131-L138)

Workaround is to create Tab wrapper component which includes both **IonTabs** and **IonTabBar**

```tsx
// TabsWrapper.tsx

const TabWrapper: React.FC<{
  items: IMenuItem[]
}> = ({
  items,
  children,
}) => (
  <IonTabs>
    {children}
    <IonTabBar slot="bottom">
      {items.map((item, index) =>
        <IonTabButton
          key={index}
          tab={index.toString()}
          href={item.url}
        >
          <IonIcon md={item.mdIcon} ios={item.iosIcon} />
          <IonLabel>{item.title}</IonLabel>
        </IonTabButton>
      )}
    </IonTabBar>
  </IonTabs>
)

export default TabWrapper
```

Usage:

```tsx
// App.tsx

import TabsWrapper from './TabsWrapper'

const menuItems = [
  // Menu items
]

const App: React.FC = () => (
  <TabsWrapper items={menuItems}>
    <IonRouterOutlet id="main">
      {/** Routes */}
    </IonRouterOutlet>
  </TabsWrapper>
)

export default App
```

Hi, I had the same wish as you and made this little scss tricks to get an extended floating action button as an angular component according to Material standards (https://material.io/components/buttons-floating-action-button).
Since ion-fab-button are not easy to customise in scss, I started from a ion-button.
Use it as you want, but keep in mind extended floating action buttons are a Material pattern and will not be appropriate in an iOS UI.

Made in Ionic 5 with Angular.

demo-page.html:
    
    <ion-content>
    
      <ion-button
        (click)="toggleExtendedFabButton()">toggle</ion-button>
      
      <ion-fab
        vertical="bottom"
        horizontal="end"
        slot="fixed">
      
      <app-extended-fab-button
        [buttonClass]="toggled ? 'extended' : ''"
        [buttonColor]="'tertiary'"
        [iconSrc]="'assets/icons/chat_filled_24dp.svg'"
        [labelValue]="'New communication'"
        ></app-extended-fab-button>
      
      </ion-fab>
    
    </ion-content>

extended-fab-button.component.scss:

    ion-button {
      width: auto;
      min-width: 56px;
      max-width: 56px;
      height: 56px;
      transition: max-width 270ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1) 0ms, height 270ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1) 0ms;
      --padding-top: 16px;
      --padding-bottom: 16px;
      --padding-start: 16px;
      --padding-end: 16px;
      --border-radius: 28px;
      --box-shadow: var(--app-box-shadow-large) !important;
      
      &.ion-activated {
        --box-shadow: var(--app-box-shadow-extra-large) !important;
      }
      
      ion-icon {
        width: 24px;
        height: 24px;
        font-size: 24px;
      }
      
      ion-label {
        width: auto;
        max-width: 0;
        padding-left: 0;
        opacity: 0;
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        transition: max-width 270ms cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1) 0ms, opacity 15ms linear 30ms;
      }
      
      &.extended {
        max-width: 256px;
        height: 48px;
        --border-radius: 24px;
        --padding-top: 12px;
        --padding-bottom: 12px;
        
        ion-label {
          max-width: calc(256px - 24px - (16px*2));
          padding-left: 16px;
          opacity: 1;
          overflow: hidden;
          white-space: nowrap;
          text-overflow: ellipsis;
        }
      }
    }
